<br>
First, let me state that I most generally consider anyone that fell in the pits someone that probably took a wrong turn. Run/walk does not affect fear movement rate and pathing while feared will not send you down a pit trap.<br>
<br>
But let's not worry about that, you fell down the pit and you're going to die. So just stand there and let nature take it's course. PLEASE! I like knowing that when I drop down to gather corpses, they will not be hard to find. If you die right were you fell in, you save me (as your corpse retriever) a lot of time.. If you run off to god knows where, I might not find you and you'll just have to start a new character or MMORPG.<br>
<br>
So, we found your corpse and the porter finally got done taking care of everyone else.. A cleric and a porter (wiz/druid) jump down. The cleric's only job is to resurect, the porter's job is to invis every time invis drops and once everyone is done, get them out. <br>
<br>
The only way out of the pits besides porting is through Vox's lair, there are things that see invis near the drop into Vox's lair so don't even try running out. <br>
<br>
Just be patient, and if in the few seconds you are visible please just die and don't expect help. You'll get another rez. Thank you for coming to Permafrost and next time, use the middle ramp only! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ualihjazanzibar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alihja Zanzibar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Admin</span><br>  Posts: 496<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(8/17/01 1:41:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Permafrost Bear Pit Corpse Recoveries</span><hr size=1> That's good, sound advice! <p>Alihja Zanzibar <br> 
